		"name": "Library Management Project",
		"description": "The **Library Management System** is a web-based application designed to efficiently manage books, users, and borrowing operations in a library. The system allows libraries to register, manage their book inventory, handle user roles, and track book requests. It provides authentication for different user roles, ensuring secure access and control over library functions.\n\n### **Key Modules & Features**\n\n#### **1\\. Authentication & User Management**\n\n- **Library Registration** (`/auth/library/signup`) – Allows library owners to register their library.\n    \n- **User Signup** (`/auth/signup`) – Enables readers to create an account.\n    \n- **Role-Based Access** – Users can be assigned as **Reader, Admin, or Owner**.\n    \n- **Admin/User Management**\n    \n    - Owners can promote users to **Admin**.\n        \n    - Admins & Owners can **view all users, fetch user details, or delete user accounts**.\n        \n\n#### **2\\. Book Inventory Management**\n\n- **View Books** – Readers & Owners can see all available books.\n    \n- **Manage Books** (Owners & Admins only)\n    \n    - **Add, Update, Delete books**.\n        \n- **Issued Books** – Users can view their issued books.\n    \n- **Book Search**\n    \n    - Search by **Title, ISBN, Publisher, or Author**.\n        \n    - Get book details by **Book ID**.\n        \n\n**3\\. Book Requests**\n\n- **Request Handling** (Readers)\n    \n    - **Issue Request** – Readers can request books for borrowing.\n        \n    - **Return Request** – Readers can request to return books.\n        \n- **Request Approval** (Owners & Admins)\n    \n    - Accept or Reject book requests.\n        \n    - Fetch all requests, get a specific request by ID, or delete a request.\n        \n\n### **Technology Stack**\n\n- **Backend**: Golang (Gin Framework)\n    \n- **Database**: PostgreSQL\n    \n- **Authentication**: JWT-based authentication\n    \n- **API Documentation**: Postman",
